ciscoRadiusExtMIB.name: ciscoRadiusExtMIB
ciscoRadiusExtMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-aaa@cisco.com
ciscoRadiusExtMIB.description: This MIB module defines objects describing RADIUS (Remote Access Dialin User Service), serving as an extension of the following MIB modules: - - RADIUS-AUTH-CLIENT-MIB [RFC4668] - RADIUS-AUTH-SERVER-MIB [RFC4669] - RADIUS-ACC-CLIENT-MIB [RFC4670] - RADIUS-ACC-SERVER-MIB [RFC4671] - RADIUS-DYNAUTH-CLIENT-MIB [RFC4672] - RADIUS-DYNAUTH-SERVER-MIB [RFC4673] - [RFC4668] D. Nelson, RADIUS Authentication Client MIB for IPv6, RFC-4668, August 2006. - [RFC4669] D. Nelson, RADIUS Authentication Server MIB for IPv6, RFC-4669, August 2006. - [RFC4670] D. Nelson, RADIUS Accounting Client MIB for IPv6, RFC-4670, August 2006. - [RFC4671] D. Nelson, RADIUS Accounting Server MIB for IPv6, RFC-4671, August 2006. - [RFC4672] S. De Cnodder, N. Jonnala, M. Chiba, RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Client MIB, RFC-4672, September 2006. - [RFC4673] S. De Cnodder, N. Jonnala, M. Chiba, RADIUS Dynamic Authorization Server MIB, RFC-4673, September 2006.

RadiusSourceIdentifier.name: RadiusSourceIdentifier
RadiusSourceIdentifier.description: This textual convention represents the range of identifers used when 'extended RADIUS source port' is configured.

creClientTotalMaxInQLength.name: creClientTotalMaxInQLength
creClientTotalMaxInQLength.description: This object indicates the maximum length of the queue which stores the incoming RADIUS packets.

creClientTotalMaxWaitQLength.name: creClientTotalMaxWaitQLength
creClientTotalMaxWaitQLength.description: This object indicates the maximum length of the queue which stores the pending RADIUS packets for which the responses are outstanding.

creClientTotalMaxDoneQLength.name: creClientTotalMaxDoneQLength
creClientTotalMaxDoneQLength.description: This object indicates the maximum length of the queue which stores those RADIUS packets for which the responses are received.

creClientTotalAccessRejects.name: creClientTotalAccessRejects
creClientTotalAccessRejects.description: This object indicates the number of access reject packets received by the RADIUS client.

creClientTotalAverageResponseDelay.name: creClientTotalAverageResponseDelay
creClientTotalAverageResponseDelay.description: This object indicates the overall response delay experienced by RADIUS packets (both authentication and accounting).

creClientSourcePortRangeStart.name: creClientSourcePortRangeStart
creClientSourcePortRangeStart.description: If the 'extended RADIUS source ports' is configured, multiple source ports are used for sending out RADIUS authentication or accounting requests. This MIB object indicates the port value from where this range starts.

creClientSourcePortRangeEnd.name: creClientSourcePortRangeEnd
creClientSourcePortRangeEnd.description: If the 'extended RADIUS source port' is configured, multiple source ports are used for sending out RADIUS authentication or accounting requests. This MIB object indicates the port value where this range ends.

creClientLastUsedSourcePort.name: creClientLastUsedSourcePort
creClientLastUsedSourcePort.description: If the 'extended RADIUS source ports' is configured, multiple source ports are used for sending out RADIUS authentication or accounting requests. This MIB object indicates the last source port that was used to send out a RADIUS authentication or accounting request.

creClientLastUsedSourceId.name: creClientLastUsedSourceId
creClientLastUsedSourceId.description: This MIB object indicates the last source identifier that was used to send out a RADIUS packet when 'extended RADIUS source ports' is configured. The source identifier is a counter that is incremented everytime a RADIUS authentication or an accounting packet is sent.

creAuthClientBadAuthenticators.name: creAuthClientBadAuthenticators
creAuthClientBadAuthenticators.description: This object indicates the number of RADIUS authentication response packets received which contained invalid authenticators.

creAuthClientUnknownResponses.name: creAuthClientUnknownResponses
creAuthClientUnknownResponses.description: This object indicates the number of unknown RADIUS authentication responses received.

creAuthClientTotalPacketsWithResponses.name: creAuthClientTotalPacketsWithResponses
creAuthClientTotalPacketsWithResponses.description: This object indicates the number of RADIUS authentication packets that received responses.

creAuthClientBufferAllocFailures.name: creAuthClientBufferAllocFailures
creAuthClientBufferAllocFailures.description: This object indicates the number of buffer allocation failures encountered during RADIUS request formation.

creAuthClientTotalResponses.name: creAuthClientTotalResponses
creAuthClientTotalResponses.description: This object indicates the number of RADIUS authentication response packets received by the RADIUS client.

creAuthClientTotalPacketsWithoutResponse.name: creAuthClientTotalPacketsWithoutResponses
creAuthClientTotalPacketsWithoutResponse.description: This object indicates the number of RADIUS authentication packets that never received a response.

creAuthClientAverageResponseDelay.name: creAuthClientAverageResponseDelay
creAuthClientAverageResponseDelay.description: This object indicates the average response delay experienced for RADIUS authentication requests.

creAuthClientMaxResponseDelay.name: creAuthClientMaxResponseDelay
creAuthClientMaxResponseDelay.description: This object indicates the maximum delay experienced for RADIUS authentication requests.

creAuthClientMaxBufferSize.name: creAuthClientMaxBufferSize
creAuthClientMaxBufferSize.description: This object indicates the maximum buffer size for RADIUS authentication packet.

creAuthClientTimeouts.name: creAuthClientTimeouts
creAuthClientTimeouts.description: This object indicates the number of timeouts that have occurred for RADIUS authentication. After a timeout the client may retry sending the request to the same server or to a different server or give up depending on the configuration.

creAuthClientDupIDs.name: creAuthClientDupIDs
creAuthClientDupIDs.description: This object indicates the number of times client has received duplicate authentication responses with the same identifier. Out of these two packets, the later packet is considered as a true match.

creAuthClientMalformedResponses.name: creAuthClientMalformedResponses
creAuthClientMalformedResponses.description: This object indicates the number of malformed RADIUS authentication responses received. Malformed packets include packets with an invalid length.

creAuthClientLastUsedSourceId.name: creAuthClientLastUsedSourceId
creAuthClientLastUsedSourceId.description: This MIB object indicates the last source identifier that was used to send out a RADIUS authentication request when 'extended RADIUS source ports' is configured. The source identifier is a counter that is incremented everytime a RADIUS authentication request is sent.

creAcctClientBadAuthenticators.name: creAcctClientBadAuthenticators
creAcctClientBadAuthenticators.description: This object indicates the number of RADIUS Accounting-Response packets received with invalid authenticators.

creAcctClientUnknownResponses.name: creAcctClientUnknownResponses
creAcctClientUnknownResponses.description: This object indicates the number of unknown RADIUS accounting responses received.

creAcctClientTotalPacketsWithResponses.name: creAcctClientTotalPacketsWithResponses
creAcctClientTotalPacketsWithResponses.description: This object indicates the number of RADIUS accounting packets that received responses.

creAcctClientBufferAllocFailures.name: creAcctClientBufferAllocFailures
creAcctClientBufferAllocFailures.description: This object indicates the number of buffer allocation failures encountered for RADIUS accounting request.

creAcctClientTotalResponses.name: creAcctClientTotalResponses
creAcctClientTotalResponses.description: This object indicates the number of RADIUS accounting response packets received by the RADIUS client.

creAcctClientTotalPacketsWithoutResponse.name: creAcctClientTotalPacketsWithoutResponses
creAcctClientTotalPacketsWithoutResponse.description: This object indicates the number of RADIUS accounting packets that never received a response.

creAcctClientAverageResponseDelay.name: creAcctClientAverageResponseDelay
creAcctClientAverageResponseDelay.description: This object indicates the average response delay experienced for RADIUS accounting.

creAcctClientMaxResponseDelay.name: creAcctClientMaxResponseDelay
creAcctClientMaxResponseDelay.description: This object indicates the maximum delay experienced for RADIUS accounting.

creAcctClientMaxBufferSize.name: creAcctClientMaxBufferSize
creAcctClientMaxBufferSize.description: This object indicates the maximum buffer size for RADIUS accounting packets.

creAcctClientTimeouts.name: creAcctClientTimeouts
creAcctClientTimeouts.description: This object indicates the number of timeouts that have occurred for RADIUS accounting. After a timeout the client may retry sending the request to the same server or to a different server or give up depending on the configuration.

creAcctClientDupIDs.name: creAcctClientDupIDs
creAcctClientDupIDs.description: This object indicates the number of times client has received duplicate accounting responses with the same identifier. Out of these two packets, the later packet is considered as a true match.

creAcctClientMalformedResponses.name: creAcctClientMalformedResponses
creAcctClientMalformedResponses.description: This object indicates the number of malformed RADIUS accounting responses received. Malformed packets include packets with an invalid length.

creAcctClientLastUsedSourceId.name: creAcctClientLastUsedSourceId
creAcctClientLastUsedSourceId.description: This MIB object indicates the last source identifier that was used to send out a RADIUS accounting request when 'extended RADIUS source ports' is configured. The source identifier is a counter that is incremented everytime a RADIUS accounting request is sent.

creMIBCompliance.name: creMIBCompliance
creMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the CISCO RADIUS Extention MIB

creClientGlobalGroup.name: creClientGlobalGroup
creClientGlobalGroup.description: Objects for providing aggregated statistics of RADIUS client.

creClientAuthenenticationGroup.name: creClientAuthenenticationGroup
creClientAuthenenticationGroup.description: Objects for providing statistics of RADIUS client authentication packets.

creClientAccountingGroup.name: creClientAccountingGroup
creClientAccountingGroup.description: Objects for providing statistics of RADIUS client accounting packets.
